#compdef rawdns
# ============================================================================
# rawdns - Raw DNS interface to the Docker API (Go, GPL-3.0)
#
# Author : Tianon Gravi (tianon)
# Upstream: https://github.com/tianon/rawdns
#
# rawdns is a tiny DNS server that translates Docker container
# names into DNS responses. Point your Docker daemon's `--dns`
# flag at rawdns (or run rawdns as the cluster DNS for a
# Docker Swarm) and every container becomes addressable by its
# name: `dig nginx.docker. @10.0.0.5` returns the container's
# current IP, even as it gets recreated. Three handler types
# per domain:
#
#   - "containers": query the Docker daemon API for each
#     incoming question, return live container IP(s); supports
#     Swarm mode (returns Swarm node IPs)
#   - "forwarding": forward to upstream nameservers
#     (recursive resolver mode); load-balanced across
#     `nameservers[]` with optional randomization
#   - "static": serve static A/AAAA/CNAME/PTR/SRV/TXT records
#     for the domain (poor-man's authoritative DNS)
#
# Architecture: miekg/dns at the protocol layer, Docker API
# v1.x client for the container handler, JSON5 config file
# with one entry per zone. Used in production by the official
# Docker Hub auto-build infrastructure (Tianon is a long-time
# Docker Hub maintainer).
#
# Usage:
#   rawdns [config.json]    - load config from given JSON file
#                             (default: example-config.json in CWD)
#
# No other CLI flags. All behavior is config-file driven.
#
# The miekg/dns lane is built on `github.com/miekg/dns`
# (declared as a direct dep at upstream go.mod HEAD and used
# from cmd/rawdns/main.go + cmd/rawdns/docker.go + cmd/rawdns/
# forwarding.go), the canonical Go DNS library by Miek Gieben
# (github.com/miekg/dns, 8200+ stars). miekg/dns is the
# *uncontested* Go DNS library - 30+ million weekly downloads
# according to the Go module graph, used by CoreDNS, Cilium,
# Hashicorp Consul, Tailscale MagicDNS, Pi-hole FTL (Go
# rewrite), Hashicorp Vault, Kubernetes' upstream DNS path,
# and roughly every other significant Go-language DNS-
# adjacent project. Miek implemented the spec corpus in 2010
# and has shepherded byte-for-byte spec conformance ever
# since - the library is the de-facto Go DNS reference impl.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 228 :: DNS server libraries (RFC 1035 + DoH/DoT/DoQ)
# Round 1383 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 228
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : hickory-dns/hickory-server   [R1382 _constellation]
#   Go      : miekg/dns                    [R1383 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : mafintosh/dns-packet         [R1384 closing]
#
# miekg/dns is structurally interesting as a *single-author
# canonical library that achieved universal adoption* - the
# pattern seen elsewhere in this hunt at Axis 215 (cespare/
# xxhash, Caleb Spare's solo project) and Axis 211 (BurntSushi
# /toml, Andrew Gallant's solo project). All three libraries
# share the same trajectory: single maintainer (or near-solo),
# minimal-API design philosophy, byte-for-byte spec compliance
# as the primary value proposition, and zero serious
# competitors despite the host-language ecosystem's general
# tendency toward fragmented per-niche libraries.
#
# The use-case coverage of miekg/dns in the Go ecosystem is
# total: every Go DNS-related project ends up depending on
# it (often via CoreDNS or Consul as intermediate consumers).
# rawdns sits at the small-scale end of the spectrum
# (lightweight Docker-aware DNS for development clusters),
# while CoreDNS sits at the large-scale end (the official
# Kubernetes cluster DNS). Same library, three orders of
# magnitude apart in scale.
# ============================================================================

_rawdns() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '*:config file:_files -g "*.(json|json5)"'
}

_rawdns "$@"
